"reviewcomment":"My boyfriend&#39;s incredibly thoughtful family purchased my boyfriend and I a voucher for what can be described as an incredible evening. Our experience at Petrus can be summed up in one word...Perfection!<br><br>The 100% French staff really looks after you. We definitely felt special. Expect to commit a lot of time to dinning. We were at Petrus for at least 3 hours.<br><br>The portion sizes are ideal. Initially, we thought we would go home hungry....6 courses later....we could barely move. My boyfriend ordered the pheasant. I would suggest you do the same, as he is still talking about it. The chocolate sphere is an absolute must. The dessert presentation can only be described as &#34;magic&#34;. Once you have dessert at Petrus, you will understand. Save room for the fantastic tea and chocolates.<br><br>The décor was a bit modern for my taste, but the food and the dining experience more than makes up for it.<br><br>I would consider Gordon Ramsay&#39;s Petrus a London must!",
