"reviewcomment":"Simply Awesome! Go here and feast!<br><br>Located in the Fulham residental area, this unassuming pub can easily fool the eye. Looking like many of the pubs around, this is one of the few pubs to hold a Michelin Star. Came here on a Sunday, so appropriately so, a Sunday roast is required. They had 2 on the menu, one as part of the specials (Venison) and the standard one (Beef). Each of the roast are recommended for 2 people and with 4 in our group, we had to get both. Here&#39;s the rundown:<br><br>Starters:<br>Bread<br>Eat the Soda Bread. It&#39;s that damn good.<br><br>Butternut squash soup with squid and garlic<br>This was amazing. It came in a small shot glass-like cups and was savory and succulent. Only wished there was more as it was a great instrument to cut through all the meats.<br><br>Harwood Arms Scotch Eggs<br>Not on the menu during our visit, but we ordered it and you should too. I haven&#39;t had scotch eggs before so I couldn&#39;t compare against anything, but this was also quite good. Slicing through the egg allowed for the gooey beautiful yolk to ooze onto the outer meat layer. <br><br>Roasts:<br>Beef<br>Beautiful pink center with an outer ring. Along with the beef&#39;s own jus, it was melt in your mouth goodness. <br><br>Venison<br>This was wrapped in bacon to keep the venison nice and moist. It also added a salty-sweetness to the game meat. Having the soup along with the venison was a great interplay to cut through the meat.<br><br>Along with the huge pieces of meat come several accompaniments. All very good in their own as well.<br><br>Accompaniments: <br>Crispy Garlic Potatoes<br>Nice potatoes that served a nice textural difference. Not only that, they were darn good with the garlic essence and spices.<br><br>Cheese Cauliflower<br>A very flavorful and another addition to the cutting through the richness of the meat.<br><br>Mushrooms &amp; Beets<br>Two separate sides, but both roasted and just simply good.<br><br>This was a lot of food and I&#39;m still missing several sides. You&#39;ll need to come extra hungry in order to be even close to finishing this behemoth of a meal. With that said, all the food was excellent and I would recommend everything above and anything else you can fit in your stomach. Absolutely amazing.",
